               <msContents>
               <summary change="#add-summary">
                  The eighth volume of the <title>Rawz̤at al-Ṣafāʼ</title> (Garden of Purity), a general history from the creation of the world to the time of the author, 
                  <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" key="person_175393012" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/175393012/">Muḥammad ibn Khāvandshāh (1433–1498)</persName>, 
                  known as <addName type="honorific" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_175393012" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/175393012/">Mīr Khvānd</addName>.  
                  Former owner <persName role="fmo ins" key="person_44733962" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/44733962/">Sir Gore Ouseley</persName> evidently added this volume and <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7313"><idno>Persian MS 807</idno></ref> to an incomplete set that he purchased from the estate sale of <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/115158185592420060185" key="person_115158185592420060185">Captain Archibald Swinton</persName>. 
                  That uniformly bound set of six volumes comprises <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_14607"><idno>Persian MS 801</idno></ref>, 
                  <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_14608">802</ref>, 
                  <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7309">803</ref>, 
                  <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7310">804</ref>, 
                  <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7311">805</ref>, and
                  <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7312">806</ref>.
                  </summary>
