                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1762" notAfter="1804"><p>Uniformly rebound with <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7314"><idno>Persian MS 808</idno></ref>, probably for <persName role="fmo ins" key="person_44733962" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/44733962/">Sir Gore Ouseley</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Abbreviated resewing on six cords, laced into <material>pasteboard</material>, edges trimmed and decorative front-bead decorative endbands sewn in red and yellow <material>silk</material> threads at head and tail. 
                           Covered in quarter British tan calfskin <material>leather</material>, tight-backed and tight-jointed, with predominantly indigo blue spot patterned marbled paper sides. stiff leaved with plain European-manufactured endleaves, with ~9 laid lines per cm and ~23 mm between chain lines.</p>
                        <decoNote type="binding"><p>Spine fully gilt, with the Earl of Munster's arms blocked in <material>gold</material> on a skiver <material>leather</material> label applied to the top panel.</p></decoNote>
                        <p><dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
                           <height></height>
                           <width></width>
                           <depth></depth>
                        </dimensions>
                        </p> 
                        <condition>Handle with caution. Exterior and board edges abraded, and joints cracked. Boxed.</condition>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
